## Day 2

### Control Signals?
- [Big] Create boolean control port signal/trigger system (status, phase-cycle-complete signal, phase reset trigger). Use orange control color. Need to think through how this might interact with MIDI controls and macro knobs. But certain internal parameters that aren't exposed through existing parameter system ( such as phase of an oscillator for a hard sync effect)

### Configuration / UX
- [Quick] Allow group deletions, but with a warning pop-up
- [Quick] "Open editor" button on docked `ComponentParameters` (and node right-click menu) to launch specialized widget as a floating KDDW dock 
- [Medium] Create a configuration menu editor for config.json
- [Medium] improve component add text search workflow, and also create a hotkey to load the menu in a floating context for convenience
- [Medium] add component isolation tool (hide all but selected components)
- [Medium] add "highlighting" logic so that selected components also light up connection paths
- [Medium] Component duplication — plain copy, and copy-with-connections
- [Medium] Specialized Widgets in component groups should all be stacked together by default in one floating window

### Component Improvements
- [Medium] Move `FileBuffer` resampling to a separate thread; add a loading indicator
- [Medium] "Arming" system for buffer loads so real-time audio isn't disrupted
- [Medium] enhancements to `BufferStreamer`: add a reset control, loop control, and midi control
- [Big] specialized widget for `BiquadFilter` that includes a graph representation for modifying parameters

### Macro Knobs (New Feature)
- *Dependency: ControlConnection/ControlPort*
- MacroControl is a panel with a basic graph node that contains outbound control ports.
- Any component with controllable parameters gets an inbound Macro assignment slot, and a corresponding indicator on the parameter control widget indicating it is controlled.
- Internally, it has a basic formula editor to convert the generic knob value towards whatever parameters it is connected to.
- It also is capable of receiving modulation input.
- The MacroKnob is also capable of receiving control input from MIDI (but probably not another MacroKnob)":TY

### Peripheral Devices
- [Big] Support Audio Input peripherals
- [Big] Allow multiple MIDI peripheral devices
- [Big] Support MIDI output peripherals

### New Components
- [Quick] `Bitcrusher` -- reduce audio resolution ( audio in, audio out)
- [Quick] `AudioSwitch` -- switch audio through output channel 0 or 1 (audio in, 2 audio out)
- [Quick] `MidiSwitch` -- leverage midi channel system? (midi in, midi out) 
- [Quick] `Quantizer` -- real time midi manipulation and routing (midi in, midi out)
- [Quick] `MidiOffset` -- set offsets note values, velocity values (midi in, midi out)
- [Medium] `PitchShifter` -- maybe buffer + real time versions?
- [Big] `Mixer` *note: investigate whether this should be a primary component or a configured GroupComponent (e.g., chained panners with some scalar controls or something)*
  
